## Agent Planning
- Project-local guidance overrides defaults.
- Task-specific specs/plans/scratch notes are temporary. Store outside committed docs (prefer `.agent/tasks/<date>-<slug>/`). Don't commit unless guidance requires. Delete on completion. Promote durable outcomes into project doc system. Don't add personal scratch paths to project `.gitignore` (covered by global ignore).
- Promote outcomes by intent: architecture → ADRs (if used); current architecture → living design docs; usage/operations/schemas → reference docs; repeatable rules → AGENTS.md; remaining work → issue/TODO system. Ask before creating new convention.
- Spec authoring: surface open questions. Never resolve silently. Before requesting spec review, list every gap-fill decision, confirm each. "Fix TBDs" means ask, not decide. Don't start plan-writing with unconfirmed decisions.
- High-level plans: ~500 lines max readability guard. Split when covering multiple independent deliverables, features, review boundaries, or verification paths. Insert spec review checkpoints between logical groups. Execution plans from written spec/design doc may exceed limit when extra length is exact code, commands, expected outputs, or commit intent preserving design intent — not vague prose substituting for specificity.
- Plan commit steps must include subject + WHY body (motivation, constraint, or design decision). Plan author writes bodies; executor follows literally. Only plan author has spec/discussion context for WHY.
- Every plan ends with "Curate history" task by plan writer, not executor. Must specify target logical commit series (reviewer view after rebase), which commits squash and why, rebase command. Falsifiable criterion: bisectability. Every final commit builds and tests pass independently.
- Track verification/manual steps explicitly. Surface human-only blockers, don't skip silently. Summarize remaining verification at completion in one message.
